[Student "S"]
{East is to play 3NT. South leads the \HJ. You try dummy's \HQ but North plays the \HK.

Winners:   \S=0  \H=1  \D=1  \C=5  Total = 7

Things do not look good. You have only one \H stopper, the \S suit is wide open, and you have to have the \D finesse to get the two extra winners you need.

First problem: Do you hold up the \HA or not?

No, don't hold up. If you do they might take 4 \S tricks immediately, then go back to \Hs. Since your only hope of making this contract is the \D finesse you should grab the \HA, play 5 rounds of \Cs then finesse for the \DK.

 Or not. 

Remember: don't hold up when it gives the defenders a good opportunity to switch.}
[Play "W"]HJ

